One of the things that impresses me the most about this supplement is its exceptional blend of ingredients. The careful selection of high-quality components truly sets it apart from other products on the market. Each ingredient plays a crucial role in promoting optimal health and well-being. From powerful antioxidants to essential vitamins and minerals, this supplement contains a comprehensive range of nutrients that support various aspects of our body's functions. It's evident that great care has been taken in formulating this product, ensuring that it provides maximum benefits. I appreciate the dedication to using top-notch ingredients, as it gives me confidence in the effectiveness and safety of this supplement.

NOW® Sleep is a combination of ingredients formulated to help you ease your mind and relax your body so you can drift naturally off into a restful sleep. NOW® Sleep uses Valerian and Hops, two herbs that have been traditionally used to promote a calm relaxed state and support rejuvenating sleep. GABA is a neurotransmitter normally produced in the brain, where its function is to ease nervous tension. NOW® Sleep thus relaxes the nervous system to help you enjoy a tranquil night and wake up refreshed and energized in the morning.

Sleep Botanical Sleep Blend is a natural sleep aid that is designed to promote relaxation and improve sleep quality. It contains various herbs and botanicals, such as valerian root, passionflower, and chamomile, that are believed to support relaxation and reduce anxiety. It may be beneficial for individuals with sleep disorders or those looking to improve their sleep quality. It is important to note that this supplement should be used in conjunction with good sleep hygiene practices, such as maintaining a consistent sleep schedule and avoiding screen time before bed.

The Chinese name of "hops" is "hops", and it has been used as a "herbal medicine" by the people since ancient times to treat coughs and tumors. The female flower ears of hops contain two special compounds, α-picic acid and β-picic acid. During the brewing process of beer, they are isomerized by heat and become water-soluble isohop ketones; α-acid can enhance the sweetness of beer In terms of taste and taste, β-acid has excellent bactericidal properties, and at the same time forms the aroma, foam and unique bitterness of beer. It is an indispensable raw material for making beer, so it is directly called "hops" (Brewers\' hops). In January 2008, the "Journal of Agricultural Research" published by the United States Department of Agriculture reported that "Forage and Grass Crops Research Institute" recently bred a new type of β-acid content as high as 13.2%, and also contains a large amount of antioxidant "bioflavones". "The hop variety can regulate the body's immunity and has the function of lowering blood sugar. It is an excellent "natural antibiotic" and can be brewed as a health drink. Therefore, the Ministry of Agriculture specially named it "hops" "Teamaker". Because of its excellent antibacterial and antiseptic properties, it has been used by the food industry as an additive in the manufacture of candy and animal feed. Dr. Warner Barker, a chemist at the Technical University of Munich in Germany, confirmed that hops also contain a healthy "xanthohumol" that can inhibit the activation of cancer cells and help eliminate "carcinogens" in the human body; hops can prevent and treat breast cancer and colon cancer. , Ovarian cancer and prostate cancer have a good effect, especially in the early stage of cancer. In addition, hops also contain a kind of "phytoestrogen", which can significantly reduce the accumulation of cholesterol in the human body. The university is studying the processing and brewing of special "anti-cancer beer" and "health beer".
